## 3. Street View Static API

### Descripción
Genera imágenes estáticas (no interactivas) de Street View vía URL HTTP. Ideal para thumbnails, reportes, emails.

### URL Base:
```
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview
```

### Parámetros:

| Parámetro | Requerido | Tipo | Descripción |
|-----------|-----------|------|-------------|
| `size` | Sí | `WxH` | Tamaño en píxeles. Máx: 640x640 |
| `location` | Sí* | `lat,lng` o texto | Ubicación (coordenadas o dirección) |
| `pano` | Sí* | string | ID del panorama (alternativa a location) |
| `heading` | No | 0-360 | Dirección de la cámara (brújula) |
| `pitch` | No | -90 a 90 | Inclinación. Default: 0 (horizontal) |
| `fov` | No | 10-120 | Campo de visión horizontal. Default: 90 |
| `radius` | No | metros | Radio de búsqueda. Default: 50 |
| `source` | No | `default`/`outdoor` | Filtro de fuente |
| `return_error_code` | No | `true`/`false` | Retornar HTTP 404 si no hay imagen |
| `key` | Sí | string | API key de Google |
| `signature` | Recom. | string | Firma digital para seguridad |

*Se requiere `location` O `pano`, no ambos.

### Ejemplos de URL:

```bash
# Por coordenadas (Av. Kennedy 7100, mirando al Este)
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?size=640x480&location=-33.4078,-70.5755&heading=90&pitch=0&fov=90&key=API_KEY

# Por dirección
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?size=640x480&location=Av+Kennedy+7100,Vitacura,Chile&heading=180&pitch=10&key=API_KEY

# Zoom in (fov pequeño = más zoom)
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?size=640x480&location=-33.4078,-70.5755&heading=90&pitch=0&fov=40&key=API_KEY

# Mirando hacia arriba (edificio)
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?size=640x480&location=-33.4078,-70.5755&heading=90&pitch=45&key=API_KEY

# Solo imágenes outdoor
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?size=640x480&location=-33.4078,-70.5755&source=outdoor&key=API_KEY
```

### Metadata API (verificar disponibilidad sin gastar cuota):
```bash
# Verificar si hay Street View disponible
https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview/metadata?location=-33.4078,-70.5755&key=API_KEY

# Respuesta:
{
  "copyright": "© Google",
  "date": "2023-03",
  "location": { "lat": -33.4078, "lng": -70.5755 },
  "pano_id": "CAoSK0FGMVFpcE...",
  "status": "OK"  // o "ZERO_RESULTS"
}
```

### Notas importantes:
- Si no hay imagen disponible, retorna imagen gris genérica (usar `return_error_code=true` para evitarlo)
- Límite: 30,000 consultas/minuto
- Tamaño máximo: 640x640 píxeles
- Las consultas de metadata NO consumen cuota

---

## 4. Map Tiles API - Street View Tiles

### Descripción
Tiles de alta resolución para renderizadores custom (Cesium, Three.js, etc.)

### Flujo de Trabajo:

```
1. Obtener session token (mapType: "streetview")
2. Buscar panoId por coordenadas
3. Obtener metadata del panorama
4. Descargar tiles individuales
5. Ensamblar panorama equirectangular
```

### Paso 1: Session Token
```bash
POST https://tile.googleapis.com/v1/createSession?key=API_KEY
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "mapType": "streetview",
  "language": "es",
  "region": "CL"
}

# Respuesta:
{
  "session": "SESSION_TOKEN",
  "expiry": "1234567890",  # Unix timestamp, válido 2 semanas
  "tileWidth": 512,
  "tileHeight": 512,
  "imageFormat": "jpeg"
}
```

### Paso 2: Buscar panoId
```bash
POST https://tile.googleapis.com/v1/streetview/panoIds?session=SESSION&key=API_KEY
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locations": [
    { "lat": -33.4078, "lng": -70.5755 },
    { "lat": -33.41, "lng": -70.53 }
  ],
  "radius": 50
}

# Respuesta:
{
  "panoIds": [
    { "panoId": "CAoSK0FGMVFpcE...", "lat": -33.4078, "lng": -70.5755 },
    { "panoId": "dE9vZ3JhcGh5...", "lat": -33.41, "lng": -70.53 }
  ]
}
```

### Paso 3: Metadata
```bash
GET https://tile.googleapis.com/v1/streetview/metadata?panoId=PANO_ID&session=SESSION&key=API_KEY

# Respuesta:
{
  "panoId": "CAoSK0FGMVFpcE...",
  "lat": -33.4078,
  "lng": -70.5755,
  "imageHeight": 6656,
  "imageWidth": 13312,
  "tileHeight": 512,
  "tileWidth": 512,
  "heading": 0,
  "tilt": 90,
  "roll": 0,
  "imageryType": "outdoor",
  "date": "2023-03",
  "copyright": "© Google",
  "links": [{ "panoId": "...", "heading": 90 }]
}
```

### Paso 4: Descargar Tiles
```bash
GET https://tile.googleapis.com/v1/streetview/tiles/{z}/{x}/{y}?session=SESSION&key=API_KEY&panoId=PANO_ID

# z = zoom level (0-5)
# x = tile column
# y = tile row
```

### Paso 5: Thumbnails (alternativa rápida)
```bash
GET https://tile.googleapis.com/v1/streetview/thumbnail?session=SESSION&key=API_KEY&panoId=PANO_ID&height=400&width=800&heading=90&pitch=0&fov=90
```

### Niveles de Zoom:
| Zoom | Resolución | Tiles |
|------|-----------|-------|
| 0 | 416×208 | 1×1 |
| 1 | 832×416 | 2×1 |
| 2 | 1664×832 | 4×2 |
| 3 | 3328×1664 | 7×4 |
| 4 | 6656×3328 | 13×7 |
| 5 | 13312×6656 | 26×13 |

---

## 5. Street View Publish API

### Descripción
Permite subir fotos 360° a Google Street View.

### Endpoints:

```bash
# Crear upload URL
POST https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photo:startUpload
Authorization: Bearer {oauth_token}

# Subir foto (PUT al uploadUrl retornado)
PUT {uploadUrl}
Content-Type: image/jpeg
Body: [bytes de la foto]

# Publicar foto
POST https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photo
Authorization: Bearer {oauth_token}
{
  "uploadReference": { "uploadUrl": "{uploadUrl}" },
  "pose": {
    "latLngPair": { "latitude": -33.4078, "longitude": -70.5755 },
    "heading": 90,
    "pitch": 0,
    "roll": 0,
    "altitude": 650
  },
  "captureTime": "2026-03-26T12:00:00Z"
}

# Obtener foto
GET https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photo/{photoId}

# Listar fotos
GET https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photos?pageSize=100

# Actualizar foto
PUT https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photo/{photoId}

# Eliminar foto
DELETE https://streetviewpublish.googleapis.com/v1/photo/{photoId}
```

### Requisitos de fotos:
- Formato: JPEG con metadata XMP Photo Sphere
- Resolución mínima: 7.5 megapíxeles (4K)
- Proyección: Equirectangular
- Relación aspecto: 2:1
- OAuth 2.0 requerido (scope: `streetviewpublish`)

---

## 6. Ejemplo Completo: Visor de Street View para Tasaciones

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>RETaxes - Visor Street View</title>
  <style>
    #map { width: 50%; height: 500px; float: left; }
    #street-view { width: 50%; height: 500px; float: left; }
    #controls { clear: both; padding: 20px; }
    .info { margin: 10px 0; font-family: Arial; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="map"></div>
  <div id="street-view"></div>
  <div id="controls">
    <div class="info" id="pano-info"></div>
    <button onclick="captureView('norte')">Vista Norte</button>
    <button onclick="captureView('sur')">Vista Sur</button>
    <button onclick="captureView('este')">Vista Este</button>
    <button onclick="captureView('oeste')">Vista Oeste</button>
    <button onclick="captureView('arriba')">Vista Arriba</button>
  </div>

  <script>
    let map, panorama, marker;

    async function initMap() {
      const { Map } = await google.maps.importLibrary("maps");
      const { StreetViewPanorama, StreetViewService } =
        await google.maps.importLibrary("streetView");
      const { AdvancedMarkerElement } = await google.maps.importLibrary("marker");

      // Ubicación: Av. Kennedy 7100
      const location = { lat: -33.4078, lng: -70.5755 };

      // Crear mapa
      map = new Map(document.getElementById("map"), {
        center: location,
        zoom: 17,
        mapId: "RETAXES_MAP"
      });

      // Crear Street View
      panorama = new StreetViewPanorama(
        document.getElementById("street-view"), {
          position: location,
          pov: { heading: 90, pitch: 0 },
          zoom: 1,
          addressControl: true,
          imageDateControl: true,
          linksControl: true,
          panControl: true,
          fullscreenControl: true
        }
      );

      // Vincular mapa con Street View
      map.setStreetView(panorama);

      // Marcador en el mapa
      marker = new AdvancedMarkerElement({
        map: map,
        position: location,
        title: "Av. Kennedy 7100"
      });

      // Eventos para capturar datos
      panorama.addListener("position_changed", () => {
        updateInfo();
      });
      panorama.addListener("pov_changed", () => {
        updateInfo();
      });
    }

    function updateInfo() {
      const pos = panorama.getPosition();
      const pov = panorama.getPov();
      const panoId = panorama.getPano();
      document.getElementById("pano-info").innerHTML = `
        <b>Pano ID:</b> ${panoId}<br>
        <b>Posición:</b> ${pos.lat().toFixed(6)}, ${pos.lng().toFixed(6)}<br>
        <b>Heading:</b> ${pov.heading.toFixed(1)}° |
        <b>Pitch:</b> ${pov.pitch.toFixed(1)}° |
        <b>Zoom:</b> ${panorama.getZoom()}
      `;
    }

    function captureView(direction) {
      const headings = {
        norte: 0, sur: 180, este: 90, oeste: 270, arriba: null
      };
      if (direction === 'arriba') {
        panorama.setPov({ heading: panorama.getPov().heading, pitch: 60 });
      } else {
        panorama.setPov({ heading: headings[direction], pitch: 0 });
      }
    }

    // Función para generar URL de imagen estática
    function getStaticUrl(lat, lng, heading, pitch, size = "640x480") {
      return `https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/streetview?` +
        `size=${size}&location=${lat},${lng}` +
        `&heading=${heading}&pitch=${pitch}&fov=90&key=API_KEY`;
    }

    initMap();
  </script>
  <script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=API_KEY&callback=initMap&v=weekly" async defer></script>
</body>
</html>
```

